id: pm-tjvl
title: Compact strict create recovery for agents
description: Reduce token-heavy strict pm create schema validation recovery output for agents while preserving detailed --explain diagnostics. Tracks GitHub issue #201.
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 1
tags: []
created_at: "2026-06-12T15:18:13.660Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-12T15:34:31.478Z"
author: codex-sdk-cli-continuation
parent: pm-mpbb
resolution: Compact strict-create recovery now emits low-token structured recovery metadata by default and expands invocation context only when --explain is requested.
expected_result: Agents receive exact missing fields and suggested flags without full attempted command echo in default --json strict-create failures; humans can request full diagnostics with --explain.
actual_result: Strict create --json returns recovery_mode=compact with missing_required_fields/suggested_flags and omits attempted_command/normalized_args; strict create --json --explain restores attempted_command and normalized_args. Focused tests and manual temp smoke passed.
